  "body": "/kind feature\r\n\r\n**What happened**:\r\nWhen an ELB is provisioned as a LoadBalancer, the client traffic's security group rule can be scoped to specific ranges but the MTU discovery rule cannot.\r\n\r\n**What you expected to happen**:\r\nThe MTU discovery security group rule source range is configurable or matches the values of `spec.loadBalancerSourceRanges`\r\n\r\n**Anything else we need to know?**:\r\nThe `0.0.0.0/0` value appears to be [hardcoded here](https://github.com/kubernetes/kubernetes/blob/release-1.10/pkg/cloudprovider/providers/aws/aws.go#L3530).\r\n\r\nI operate in an environment where `0.0.0.0/0` as a source range is generally disallowed.\r\n\r\n**Environment**:\r\n- Kubernetes version (use `kubectl version`): 1.10.1\r\n- Cloud provider or hardware configuration: AWS\r\n- Others: ELB, not using ALB in this case\r\n",
